IRS990.Desc: CENTRO MATER CHILD CARE SERVICES, INC. IS PART OF CATHOLIC HEALTH SERVICES AND SERVES CHILDREN AND FAMILIES IN MIAMI DADE COUNTY. ALL FIVE CENTRO MATER CENTERS REMAIN ACCREDITED BY THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION FOR EARLY CHILDHOOD (NAEYC). CENTRO MATER EAST AFTER-SCHOOL PROGRAMS MAINTAINED THE NATIONAL ACCREDITATION FROM THE COUNCIL OF ACCREDITATION. PRESENTLY, OUR AFTERSCHOOL PROGRAM IS THE ONLY ONE IN SOUTH FLORIDA WITH THIS NATIONAL ACCREDITATION. CENTRO MATER CHILDCARE SERVICES SERVES A MONTHLY AVERAGE OF 1,200 CHILDREN AND OVER 1,900 UNDUPLICATED CHILDREN DURING THIS FISCAL YEAR 2021-22. CENTRO MATER EARLY HEAD START PROGRAM HAS A FUNDED ENROLLMENT OF 142 CHILDREN AND SERVED 184. AT THE END OF THE PROGRAM YEAR, OVER 97.1% OF THE CHILDREN WERE UP TO DATE WITH ALL POSSIBLE IMMUNIZATIONS, 99% HAD ACCESS TO MEDICAL, 98% TO DENTAL SERVICES AND 99.2% WERE ENROLLED IN HEALTH INSURANCE. CENTRO MATER HEAD START PROGRAM HAS A FUNDED ENROLLMENT WAS 526 CHILDREN AND WE SERVED 572. AT THE END OF THE PROGRAM YEAR, 99.2% OF CHILDREN WERE UP TO DATE WITH ALL POSSIBLE IMMUNIZATIONS AND OVER 96.5% WERE UP TO DATE ON SCHEDULE OF PREVENTATIVE AND PRIMARY HEALTH CARE PER THE STATE'S EPSDT SCHEDULE. AT THE END OF THE PROGRAM YEAR, ALL CHILDREN HAD ACCESS TO AN ONGOING SOURCE OF CONTINUOUS HEALTH CARE AND 99.8% WERE ENROLLED IN HEALTH INSURANCE. THE AGENCY EXCEEDED THE REQUIREMENT OF SERVING AT LEAST 10% OF CHILDREN WITH DISABILITY FOR EARLY HEAD START (22%). CENTRO MATER'S AFTERSCHOOL PROGRAM SERVED OVER 455 CHILDREN DURING THE SCHOOL YEAR THROUGH THE CHILDREN'S TRUST GRANT. DURING THE SUMMER, WE SUCCESSFULLY PROVIDED IN-PERSON SERVICES FOR APPROXIMATELY 698 CHILDREN ENROLLED IN CHILDREN'S TRUST SUMMER PROGRAM.CENTRO MATER RECEIVED THE RECOGNITION AS BEST PROGRAM ATTENDANCE GIVEN BY MIAMI DADE COUNTY OFFICE OF HEAD START.CENTRO MATER EAST BASEBALL TEAM COMPLETED ITS BASEBALL SEASON SPONSORED BY THE MIAMI MARLINS.CENTRO MATER EAST SOCCER TEAM INAUGURATED THE FIRST MINI SOCCER PITCH.CENTRO MATER HEATER PROGRAM WAS EXTENDED TO ALL THE SITES AND RECEIVED HIGH MARKS OF ACHIEVEMENT BY MIAMI DADE CULTURAL AFFAIRS.ALL STAFF RECEIVED A BONUS FOR THE END OF THE SCHOOL YEAR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS ADOPTED THE PROVISIONS OF ASC NO 740, "ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES" ("ASC NO 740"). ASC 740 REQUIRED THAT THE IMPACT OF TAX POSITIONS TO BE RECOGNIZED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS IF THEY ARE MORE LIKELY THAN NOT OF BEING SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION. ACCORDINGLY, NO PROVISION FOR INCOME TAXES IS MADE IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. AT 6/30/23, THERE WERE NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS. THE ORGANIZATION FILES TAX RETURNS WITH US FEDERAL AND OTHER TAX AUTHORITIES FOR WHICH STATUE LIMITATIONS MAY GO BACK TO THE YEAR ENDED 2020.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE SOLE MEMBER HAS THE RIGHT TO APPOINT THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND TO DETERMINE ANY MATTER WHICH MAY BE PROPERLY BROUGHT BEFORE THE MEMBERS FOR ACTION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CORPORATE CONTROLLER AND THE CFO CONDUCTS A COMPREHENSIVE REVIEW OF THE FORM 990 BEFORE IT IS FILED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL EMPLOYEES AND DIRECTORS ARE COVERED BY THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND ARE PROVIDED WITH THE POLICY UPON HIRE. THE POLICY IS REVIEWED ANNUALLY BY THE CORPORATE COMPLIANCE OFFICER, WHO ALSO DETERMINES WHETHER A CONFLICT MAY EXIST PER POLICY. EMPLOYEES ARE REQUIRED TO DISCLOSE ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST IF A CONFLICT OF INTEREST OCCURS, IT IS INVESTIGATED AND THE RESULTS ARE REPORTED TO THE GOVERNING BODY. LEGAL AND DISCIPLINARY ACTION AND RESTRICTIONS ARE IDENTIFIED ON AN INDIVIDUAL BASIS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS DETERMINES THE COMPENSATION AND BENEFITS OF THE TOP OFFICIALS. THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS IS INDEPENDENT WITH RESPECT TO COMPENSATION AND BENEFITS. TOTAL COMPENSATION ANALYSIS IS CONDUCTED BY AN INDEPENDENT CONSULTANT WHO PROVIDES DATA TO COMPARE COMPENSATION AND BENEFITS FOR SIMILIAR POSITIONS WITHIN THE INDUSTRY. COMPENSATION AND BENEFIT CHANGES FOR THE TOP OFFICIALS ARE DISCUSSED IN THE BOARD MEETINGS AND ARE PROPERLY DOCUMENTED IN THE MINUTES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE FOR PUBLIC INSPECTION UPON REQUEST.
